  "prompt": "I am using a Moto G, and it failed to download the OTA update of Android due to a network error. Now what can I do to get it updated?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to update your Moto G if the OTA update failed:\n\n1. Check Network Connection\n- Ensure stable Wi-Fi or mobile data connection\n- Try downloading update on different network\n- Restart router or mobile data\n\n2. Manual OTA Update\n- Go to Settings > System > System Update\n- Tap \"Check for updates\" again\n- If it still fails, wait and retry later\n\n3. Download Update Manually\n- Visit Motorola's official website\n- Find firmware for your specific Moto G model\n- Download firmware file to computer\n- Transfer to phone via USB\n- Install through recovery mode\n\n4. Use Motorola Update Services\n- Connect phone to Wi-Fi\n- Go to Settings > System > System Update\n- If option available, select \"Download via PC\"\n- Follow Motorola's instructions\n\n5. Factory Reset (Last Resort)\n- Backup all data\n- Go to Settings > System > Reset options\n- Select Factory reset\n- After reset, try updating again\n\n6. Check Storage Space\n- Ensure enough free storage for update\n- Delete unnecessary files/apps\n- Free up minimum 1-2 GB space\n\nIf none work, contact Motorola support for specific guidance.",
